ts in various government ministries, departments, and organizations through the SSC CGL Exam. The list of&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: center; color: inherit;\">SSC CGL Posts&nbsp;</span>and their classification, along with the related Department/Ministry, is tabulated below.</p><figure class=\"table\" style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); margin-bottom: 1rem; --bs-table-bg: transparent; --bs-table-striped-color: #212529; --bs-table-striped-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); --bs-table-active-color: #212529; --bs-table-active-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); --bs-table-hover-color: #212529; --bs-table-hover-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.075); width: 892px; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230); font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><table style=\"width: 892px;\"><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px; text-align: center; width: 891.2px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">SSC CGL Posts List</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">SSC CGL Post</span></td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 188px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Classification of Post</span></td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Department/Ministry</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Assistant Section Officer</td><td rowspan=\"8\" style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 188px;\">Group “B”</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">Central Secretariat Service, Intelligence Bureau, Ministry of Railway, Ministry of External Affairs, AFHQ</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Assistant</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">Other Ministries/ Departments/ Organizations</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Inspector (Central Excise)</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">CBIC</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Assistant Enforcement Officer</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">Directorate of Enforcement, Department of Revenue</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Sub Inspector</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">Central Bureau of Investigation</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Inspector</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">Central Bureau of Narcotics</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Junior Statistical Officer</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">M/o Statistics &amp; Programme Implementation</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Statistical Investigator Grade-II</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">Registrar General of India</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Inspector of Income Tax</td><td rowspan=\"5\" style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 188px;\">Group “C”</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">CBDT</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Auditor</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">Offices under C&amp;AG, CGDA</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Accountant/ Junior Accountant</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">Other Ministry/ Departments</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Senior Secretariat Assistant/ Upper Division Clerks</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">Central Govt. Offices/ Ministries other than CSCS cadres</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 232.125px;\">Tax Assistant</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; width: 471.075px;\">CBDT/ CBIC</td></tr></tbody></table></figure></h5><h2 id=\"UGF9F5M5EBEEE1EF63CWKPE2IWNB247G\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); display: inline-block; width: 892px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">SSC CGL Preparation Tips</h2><h5 class=\"pt20 bluc\" style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.25rem; padding-top: 20px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font style=\"\">Candidates must focus on the strategic approach when beginning the preparation for the SSC CGL Exams. The candidates who scored well in the exams and secured the positions in previous years have shared a few&nbsp;</font><span style=\"text-align: center;\">S</span><span style=\"text-align: center;\">SC CGL Preparation Tips&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);\">that every candidate must follow-</span></p><figure class=\"table\" style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); margin-bottom: 1rem; --bs-table-bg: transparent; --bs-table-striped-color: #212529; --bs-table-striped-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); --bs-table-active-color: #212529; --bs-table-active-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); --bs-table-hover-color: #212529; --bs-table-hover-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.075); width: 892px; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230); font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><table style=\"width: 892px;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Preparation Tips</span></td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Details</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Understand the Exam Pattern, Syllabus and Marking Scheme</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Begin by understanding the SSC CGL exam pattern, including the subjects, number of questions, marking scheme, and time allocation for each section. This understanding will help you create a structured study plan.</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Create an Effective Study Plan</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">As we all know that the SSC CGL Exam Date has been announced so it becomes important to develop an effective study plan and candidates must give sufficient time for each subject.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Collect Authentic Study Material &amp; Books</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">To prepare effectively for the SSC CGL&nbsp; exam, selecting authentic and high-quality study materials and books is crucial, given the competitive nature of the exam</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Subject-wise Preparation Strategy&nbsp;</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Candidates can also prepare a strategy for each subject (General Awareness, Reasoning, Quantitative Aptitude and English Language). More time is to be given to the subject in which you are weak.</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Add Mock Tests and SSC CGL Previous Year Question Papers in your preparation</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The most important part is practising with&nbsp;</span><font style=\"\" color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">SSC CGL Mock Test</span></font><span style=\"color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;and Previous Year Papers to understand the pattern of questions asked in previous exams and what could be expected in the upcoming exams.&nbsp;</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Focus on Time Management</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Time management is very important for SSC CGL&nbsp; preparation and performance, as the exam is of 60 minutes duration for solving 100 questions. Allocate 6–8 hours daily, balancing all subjects based on strengths and weaknesses.</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Prepare Notes and Revise Timely&nbsp;</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">During preparation candidates must not miss preparing notes as this helps in quick revision before the exam.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Read Newspapers and Go through Current Affairs (Daily/Weekly/Monthly)</td><td style=\"border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Do not miss reading newspapers and collecting information on current events as there are 25 questions from general awareness section.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure></h5>', 3, '2026-01-07 07:21:40', '2026-01-29 09:21:10');
INSERT INTO `bank_po_exam_tabs` (`id`, `exam_id`, `tab_title`, `tab_content`, `display_order`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(20, 7, 'Eligibility Criteria', '\r\n\r\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\r\n  <title>SBI Clerk (Junior Associates) Eligibility Criteria</title>\r\n  <style>\r\n    body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;margin:20px;color:#111}\r\n    .wrap{max-width:1050px}\r\n    .card{border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:10px;padding:14px;margin:14px 0}\r\n    h1{margin:0 0 10px}\r\n    h2{margin:0 0 8px}\r\n    h3{margin:12px 0 6px}\r\n    p{margin:8px 0}\r\n    table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:10px}\r\n    th,td{border:1px solid #ddd;padding:8px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}\r\n    th{background:#f6f6f6}\r\n    .note{background:#fff7e6;border:1px solid #ffe2a8;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin-top:10px}\r\n  </style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"wrap\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h1>SBI Clerk Eligibility Criteria</h1>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The eligibility criteria of the SBI Clerk exam are mainly based on two pre-requisites:\r\n        <b>Educational Qualification</b> and <b>Age Limit</b>.\r\n      </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h2>SBI Clerk Educational Qualifications</h2>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The candidate must hold a valid graduation degree (UG) in any discipline from a recognised University\r\n        or any equivalent qualification recognised as such by the Central Government.\r\n      </p>\r\n      <p>\r\n        Candidates having integrated dual degree (IDD) certificates should ensure that the date of passing the IDD\r\n        meets the eligibility requirements.\r\n      </p>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"note\">\r\n        <b>Note:</b> Candidates in the final year/semester of graduation may also apply.\r\n        If provisionally selected, they will be required to produce proof of having passed the graduation examination.\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h2>SBI Clerk Age Limit</h2>\r\n      <p>\r\n        Not below <b>20 years</b> and not above <b>28 years</b>, i.e. candidates must have been born\r\n        not earlier than <b>02.04.1997</b> and not later than <b>01.04.2005</b> (both days inclusive).\r\n      </p>\r\n\r\n      <h3>Upper Age Limit Relaxation</h3>\r\n      <table>\r\n        <tbody><tr>\r\n          <th>S. No.</th>\r\n          <th>Category</th>\r\n          <th>Upper Age Limit Relaxation</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr><td>1</td><td>OBC</td><td>3 years</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>2</td><td>SC/ST</td><td>5 years</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>3</td><td>Person with disabilities (General/EWS)</td><td>10 years</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>4</td><td>Person with disabilities (OBC)</td><td>13 years</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>5</td><td>Person with disabilities (SC/ST)</td><td>15 years</td></tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td>6</td>\r\n          <td>Ex-Servicemen / Disabled Ex-Servicemen</td>\r\n          <td>\r\n            Actual period of service rendered in defence services + 3 years\r\n            (8 years for Disabled Ex-servicemen belonging to SC/ST),\r\n            subject to maximum age of 50 years\r\n          </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td>7</td>\r\n          <td>Widows, Divorced women (Not remarried)</td>\r\n          <td>\r\n            7 years (subject to maximum age of 35 years for General/EWS,\r\n            38 years for OBC &amp; 40 years for SC/ST candidates)\r\n          </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td>8</td>\r\n          <td>Trained Apprentice of SBI</td>\r\n          <td>\r\n            General/EWS - 1 year<br>\r\n            OBC - 4 years<br>\r\n            SC/ST - 6 years<br>\r\n            PwBD (Gen/EWS) - 11 years<br>\r\n            PwBD (OBC) - 14 years<br>\r\n            PwBD (SC/ST) - 16 years\r\n          </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n      </tbody></table></div><div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"card\">\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div><style>\r\n    body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;margin:20px;color:#111}\r\n    .wrap{max-width:1100px}\r\n    .card{border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:12px;padding:16px;margin:14px 0}\r\n    h1{margin:0 0 10px}\r\n    h2{margin:0 0 8px}\r\n    h3{margin:12px 0 6px}\r\n    p{margin:8px 0}\r\n    ul{margin:6px 0 0 18px}\r\n    table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:10px}\r\n    th,td{border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}\r\n    th{background:#f6f6f6}\r\n    .note{background:#fff7e6;border:1px solid #ffe2a8;border-radius:12px;padding:12px;margin-top:10px}\r\n    .muted{color:#444;font-size:14px}\r\n    .badge{display:inline-block;border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:999px;padding:2px 10px;font-size:12px;margin-right:6px}\r\n    .two-col{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:12px}\r\n    @media (max-width:820px){.two-col{grid-template-columns:1fr}}\r\n  </style>', 2, '2026-01-07 07:41:20', '2026-02-18 07:33:43'),
(21, 7, 'Exam Pattern', '\r\n\r\n\r\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\r\n  <title>SBI Clerk Prelims Exam Pattern</title>\r\n  <style>\r\n    body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;margin:20px;color:#111}\r\n    .wrap{max-width:1000px}\r\n    .card{border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:10px;padding:14px;margin:14px 0}\r\n    h1{margin:0 0 10px}\r\n    h2{margin:0 0 8px}\r\n    p{margin:8px 0}\r\n    table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:10px}\r\n    th,td{border:1px solid #ddd;padding:8px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}\r\n    th{background:#f6f6f6}\r\n    ul{margin:6px 0 0 18px}\r\n    .note{background:#fff7e6;border:1px solid #ffe2a8;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin-top:10px}\r\n  </style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"wrap\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h1>SBI Clerk Prelims Exam</h1>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The SBI Clerk Prelims exam will be conducted on <b>20th, 21st, and 27th September</b> to select eligible candidates\r\n        for the posts of <b>Junior Associates (Customer Support and Sales)</b> in branches of the State Bank of India across\r\n        the country.\r\n      </p>\r\n      <p>\r\n        Banking aspirants must be well aware of the latest SBI Clerk exam pattern set by SBI for shortlisting eligible\r\n        candidates. Understanding the exam pattern and syllabus gives a clear idea about the exam format and selection process.\r\n      </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h2>SBI Clerk Exam Pattern</h2>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The SBI Clerk selection process consists of:\r\n      </p>\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <li>Two online tests: <b>Preliminary</b> and <b>Main</b> examination</li>\r\n        <li>A test of a specified <b>local language</b></li>\r\n      </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h2>SBI Clerk Prelims Exam Pattern</h2>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The Preliminary Examination (online) consists of objective tests for <b>100 marks</b>. The test is of\r\n        <b>1 hour</b> duration and has <b>3 sections</b> as follows:\r\n      </p>\r\n\r\n      <table>\r\n        <tbody><tr>\r\n          <th>S. No.</th>\r\n          <th>Section</th>\r\n          <th>No. of Questions</th>\r\n          <th>Total Marks</th>\r\n          <th>Duration</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr><td>1</td><td>English Language</td><td>30</td><td>30</td><td>20 minutes</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>2</td><td>Numerical Ability</td><td>35</td><td>35</td><td>20 minutes</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>3</td><td>Reasoning</td><td>35</td><td>35</td><td>20 minutes</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><th colspan=\"2\">Total</th><th>100</th><th>100</th><th>60 minutes</th></tr>\r\n      </tbody></table>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"note\">\r\n        <b>Note:</b> The prelims exam is conducted online and follows an objective-type pattern.\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\n\r\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\r\n  <title>SBI Clerk Prelims &amp; Mains Exam Pattern</title>\r\n  <style>\r\n    body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;margin:20px;color:#111}\r\n    .wrap{max-width:1100px}\r\n    .card{border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:10px;padding:14px;margin:14px 0}\r\n    h1{margin:0 0 10px}\r\n    h2{margin:0 0 8px}\r\n    h3{margin:12px 0 6px}\r\n    p{margin:8px 0}\r\n    ul,ol{margin:6px 0 0 18px}\r\n    table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:10px}\r\n    th,td{border:1px solid #ddd;padding:8px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}\r\n    th{background:#f6f6f6}\r\n    .note{background:#fff7e6;border:1px solid #ffe2a8;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin-top:10px}\r\n  </style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"wrap\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h1>SBI Clerk Prelims Exam Pattern - Important Points</h1>\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <li>Each test will have a separate timing as mentioned in the exam pattern.</li>\r\n        <li>\r\n          There will be negative marks for wrong answers in the objective tests.\r\n          <b>1/4th</b> of the mark assigned for the question will be deducted for each wrong answer.\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>No minimum qualifying marks for the individual subjects as well as for aggregate (overall) are prescribed.</li>\r\n        <li>\r\n          An adequate number of candidates in each category (approximately <b>10 times</b> the number of vacancies,\r\n          subject to availability) will be shortlisted for the Main Examination based on aggregate marks\r\n          in descending order.\r\n        </li>\r\n      </ul>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h2>SBI Clerk Mains Exam Pattern</h2>\r\n      <p>The structure of the main examination (online objective type) is as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n      <table>\r\n        <tbody><tr>\r\n          <th>S. No.</th>\r\n          <th>Sections</th>\r\n          <th>No. of Questions</th>\r\n          <th>Total Marks</th>\r\n          <th>Duration</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr><td>1</td><td>General English</td><td>40</td><td>40</td><td>35 minutes</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>2</td><td>Quantitative Aptitude</td><td>50</td><td>50</td><td>45 minutes</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>3</td><td>Reasoning Ability and Computer Aptitude</td><td>50</td><td>60</td><td>45 minutes</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><td>4</td><td>General/Financial Awareness</td><td>50</td><td>50</td><td>35 minutes</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><th colspan=\"2\">Total</th><th>190</th><th>200</th><th>2 hours 40 minutes</th></tr>\r\n      </tbody></table>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"note\">\r\n        <b>Negative Marking:</b> 1/4th mark will be deducted for each wrong answer in objective tests.\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h2>SBI Clerk Mains Exam Pattern - Important Points</h2>\r\n      <ol>\r\n        <li>Each test will have separate timing as mentioned above.</li>\r\n        <li>\r\n          Questions in objective tests (except General English) will be bilingual: <b>English &amp; Hindi</b>.\r\n          Negative marking applies: <b>1/4th</b> mark deducted for each wrong answer.\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>\r\n          Candidates are required to score a minimum percentage marks on aggregate\r\n          (For <b>SC/ST/OBC/PWD/XS</b> candidates, <b>5%</b> relaxation is available).\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>Minimum qualifying marks on aggregate will be decided by the bank.</li>\r\n        <li>No minimum qualifying marks for individual subjects are prescribed.</li>\r\n        <li>Merit list will be drawn <b>State-wise</b> and <b>category-wise</b>.</li>\r\n        <li>\r\n          Candidates qualified in the mains exam will be placed according to their aggregate marks\r\n          in descending order in respective States and Categories.\r\n        </li>\r\n      </ol>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\r\n  <title>SBI Clerk - Language Proficiency Test (LLPT)</title>\r\n  <style>\r\n    body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;margin:20px;color:#111}\r\n    .wrap{max-width:900px}\r\n    .card{border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:10px;padding:14px;margin:14px 0}\r\n    h1{margin:0 0 10px}\r\n    p{margin:8px 0}\r\n    table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:10px}\r\n    th,td{border:1px solid #ddd;padding:8px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}\r\n    th{background:#f6f6f6}\r\n    .note{background:#fff7e6;border:1px solid #ffe2a8;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin-top:10px}\r\n  </style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"wrap\">\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h1>SBI Clerk: Language Proficiency Test (LLPT)</h1>\r\n      <p>\r\n        Provisionally selected candidates who have <b>not studied</b> (in Class 10th or 12th) any of the specified local\r\n        language of the state applied for, will have to appear in the <b>Local Language Proficiency Test (LLPT)</b>.\r\n      </p>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"note\">\r\n        The pattern of the LLPT is given below.\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <table>\r\n        <tbody><tr>\r\n          <th>S. No.</th>\r\n          <th>Test Pattern</th>\r\n          <th>Section</th>\r\n          <th>No. of Passages</th>\r\n          <th>No. of Questions</th>\r\n          <th>Max. Marks</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td rowspan=\"2\">1</td>\r\n          <td rowspan=\"2\">Non-Verbal Test</td>\r\n          <td>Objective</td>\r\n          <td>3</td>\r\n          <td>15</td>\r\n          <td>15</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td>Subjective</td>\r\n          <td>3</td>\r\n          <td>15</td>\r\n          <td>15</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td>2</td>\r\n          <td>Verbal Test</td>\r\n          <td>--</td>\r\n          <td>--</td>\r\n          <td>20</td>\r\n          <td>--</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n      </tbody></table>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>', 3, '2026-01-07 07:41:20', '2026-01-22 10:05:25'),
(22, 7, 'Exam Syllabus', '\r\n\r\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\r\n  <title>SBI Clerk Syllabus</title>\r\n  <style>\r\n    body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;margin:20px;color:#111}\r\n    .wrap{max-width:1050px}\r\n    .card{border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:10px;padding:14px;margin:14px 0}\r\n    h1{margin:0 0 10px}\r\n    h2{margin:0 0 8px}\r\n    p{margin:8px 0}\r\n    table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:10px}\r\n    th,td{border:1px solid #ddd;padding:8px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}\r\n    th{background:#f6f6f6}\r\n    ul{margin:6px 0 0 18px}\r\n    .note{background:#fff7e6;border:1px solid #ffe2a8;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin-top:10px}\r\n  </style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"wrap\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h1>SBI Clerk Syllabus</h1>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The SBI Clerk exam includes two phases of the selection process: <b>Prelims</b> and <b>Mains</b>.\r\n        Candidates planning to appear for the SBI Clerk exam must be aware of the syllabus to plan a strategic\r\n        preparation and increase their chances of qualifying.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h2>SBI Clerk Syllabus (Overview)</h2>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The SBI Clerk syllabus is similar to that of other bank exams. The syllabus for both Prelims and Mains includes:\r\n      </p>\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <li>Reasoning Ability</li>\r\n        <li>Numerical Ability</li>\r\n        <li>English Language</li>\r\n      </ul>\r\n      <p>\r\n        For the Mains exam, <b>General Awareness</b> and <b>Computer Aptitude</b> are additionally included.\r\n        It is recommended that candidates check the syllabus and exam structure before starting preparation.\r\n      </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h2>SBI Clerk Syllabus - Key Details</h2>\r\n      <table>\r\n        <tbody><tr><th>Bank Name</th><td>State Bank of India (SBI)</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><th>Exam Name</th><td>SBI Clerk (Junior Associates)</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><th>Mode of Exam</th><td>Online</td></tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <th>SBI Clerk Exam Date</th>\r\n          <td>\r\n            Prelims - 20th, 21st, &amp; 27th September 2025<br>\r\n            Mains - 21st November 2025\r\n          </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr><th>No. of Questions</th><td>Prelims - 100<br>Mains - 190</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><th>Exam Duration</th><td>Prelims - 1 hour<br>Mains - 2 hours 40 minutes</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><th>Negative Marking</th><td>¼th mark (0.25 marks)</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><th>Selection Process</th><td>Prelims - Mains - Local Language Proficiency Test</td></tr>\r\n        <tr><th>Official Website</th><td>www.sbi.co.in</td></tr>\r\n      </tbody></table>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"note\">\r\n        <b>Note:</b> Dates and vacancy numbers are shown exactly as provided in your text.\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\n\r\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\r\n  <title>SBI Clerk Selection Process</title>\r\n  <style>\r\n    body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;margin:20px;color:#111}\r\n    .wrap{max-width:950px}\r\n    .card{border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:10px;padding:14px;margin:14px 0}\r\n    h1{margin:0 0 10px}\r\n    h2{margin:0 0 8px}\r\n    p{margin:8px 0}\r\n    ol{margin:6px 0 0 18px}\r\n    .note{background:#fff7e6;border:1px solid #ffe2a8;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin-top:10px}\r\n  </style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"wrap\">\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h1>SBI Clerk Selection</h1>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The State Bank of India conducts a multi-stage selection process for SBI Clerk recruitment.\r\n        To get selected for the SBI Clerk (Junior Associate) post, candidates need to qualify in both\r\n        online tests: <b>Prelims</b> and <b>Mains</b>, followed by <b>LLPT</b>.\r\n      </p>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The <b>Local Language Proficiency Test (LLPT)</b> is <b>qualifying in nature</b>.\r\n        The marks scored in the <b>Mains exam</b> will be counted for the final selection.\r\n      </p>\r\n\r\n      <h2>Selection Stages</h2>\r\n      <ol>\r\n        <li>\r\n          <b>Stage 1 - Preliminary Examination:</b><br>\r\n          100 Questions of 100 Marks to be solved in 60 minutes\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>\r\n          <b>Stage 2 - Mains Examination:</b><br>\r\n          190 Questions of 200 Marks to be solved in 2 hours 40 minutes\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>\r\n          <b>Stage 3 - Local Language Proficiency Test (LLPT):</b><br>\r\n          Candidates who have not studied (in Class 10th or 12th) any of the specified local language of the state\r\n          applied for, will have to appear in LLPT.\r\n        </li>\r\n      </ol>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"note\">\r\n        <b>Note:</b> LLPT is qualifying only. Final selection is based on Mains marks.\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\r\n  <title>SBI Clerk Prelims &amp; Mains Syllabus</title>\r\n  <style>\r\n    body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;margin:20px;color:#111}\r\n    .wrap{max-width:1200px}\r\n    .card{border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:10px;padding:14px;margin:14px 0}\r\n    h1{margin:0 0 10px}\r\n    h2{margin:0 0 8px}\r\n    h3{margin:12px 0 6px}\r\n    p{margin:8px 0}\r\n    table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:10px}\r\n    th,td{border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}\r\n    th{background:#f6f6f6}\r\n    ul{margin:6px 0 0 18px}\r\n    .grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:12px;margin-top:10px}\r\n    .box{border:1px solid #e6e6e6;border-radius:10px;padding:12px}\r\n    .box h4{margin:0 0 6px;font-size:16px}\r\n  </style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"wrap\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h1>SBI Clerk Prelims Syllabus</h1>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The preliminary examination syllabus of the SBI Clerk exam comprises questions from\r\n        <b>Reasoning Ability</b>, <b>Numerical Ability</b>, and <b>English Language</b>.\r\n        Candidates should focus on each subject to score well in prelims and improve their chances of qualifying for mains.\r\n      </p>\r\n\r\n      <table>\r\n        <tbody><tr>\r\n          <th>English Language Syllabus</th>\r\n          <th>Reasoning Syllabus</th>\r\n          <th>Numerical Ability Syllabus</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td>\r\n            <ul>\r\n              <li>Reading Comprehension</li>\r\n              <li>Cloze Test</li>\r\n              <li>Para Jumbles</li>\r\n              <li>Miscellaneous</li>\r\n              <li>Fill in the Blanks</li>\r\n              <li>Multiple Meaning</li>\r\n              <li>Paragraph Completion</li>\r\n              <li>Error Detection</li>\r\n              <li>Misspelt</li>\r\n              <li>Word/Sentence Rearrangement</li>\r\n              <li>Single Fillers</li>\r\n              <li>Match the Column</li>\r\n              <li>Para Jumble</li>\r\n              <li>Word Usage</li>\r\n              <li>Word Swap</li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n          </td>\r\n\r\n          <td>\r\n            <ul>\r\n              <li>Logical Reasoning</li>\r\n              <li>Alphanumeric Series</li>\r\n              <li>Ranking/Direction/Alphabet Test</li>\r\n              <li>Data Sufficiency</li>\r\n              <li>Coded Inequalities</li>\r\n              <li>Seating Arrangement</li>\r\n              <li>Puzzle</li>\r\n              <li>Tabulation</li>\r\n              <li>Syllogism</li>\r\n              <li>Blood Relations</li>\r\n              <li>Input Output</li>\r\n              <li>Coding Decoding</li>\r\n              <li>Direction</li>\r\n              <li>Letter/Digit/Mix Series</li>\r\n              <li>Pair Formation</li>\r\n              <li>Meaningful Word</li>\r\n              <li>Odd One Out</li>\r\n              <li>Inequality</li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n          </td>\r\n\r\n          <td>\r\n            <ul>\r\n              <li>Simplification</li>\r\n              <li>Profit &amp; Loss</li>\r\n              <li>Mixtures &amp; Alligations</li>\r\n              <li>Simple Interest &amp; Compound Interest</li>\r\n              <li>Surds &amp; Indices</li>\r\n              <li>Work &amp; Time</li>\r\n              <li>Time &amp; Distance</li>\r\n              <li>Mensuration (Cylinder, Cone, Sphere)</li>\r\n              <li>Data Interpretation</li>\r\n              <li>Ratio &amp; Proportion</li>\r\n              <li>Percentage</li>\r\n              <li>Number Systems</li>\r\n              <li>Sequence &amp; Series</li>\r\n              <li>Permutation, Combination &amp; Probability</li>\r\n              <li>Wrong/Missing Number Series</li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n          </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n      </tbody></table>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"card\">\r\n      <h2>SBI Clerk Mains Syllabus</h2>\r\n      <p>\r\n        The Mains Examination consists of 4 sections: <b>Reasoning &amp; Computer Awareness</b>,\r\n        <b>General English</b>, <b>General/Financial Awareness</b>, and <b>Quantitative Aptitude</b>.\r\n        The detailed syllabus is given below.\r\n      </p>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"grid\">\r\n        <div class=\"box\">\r\n          <h4>Quantitative Aptitude</h4>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Simplification</li>\r\n            <li>Number Series</li>\r\n            <li>Data Sufficiency</li>\r\n            <li>Data Interpretation</li>\r\n            <li>Quadratic Equation</li>\r\n            <li>Time &amp; Distance, Work</li>\r\n            <li>Partnership</li>\r\n            <li>Profit &amp; Loss</li>\r\n            <li>Simple &amp; Compound Interest</li>\r\n            <li>Mixture and Allegations</li>\r\n            <li>Ratio &amp; Proportion</li>\r\n            <li>Averages</li>\r\n            <li>Percentages</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"box\">\r\n          <h4>General English</h4>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Reading Comprehension (Synonyms/Antonyms)</li>\r\n            <li>Sentence Rearrangement</li>\r\n            <li>Para Jumbles</li>\r\n            <li>Sentence Correction</li>\r\n            <li>Error Finding</li>\r\n            <li>Spell Checks</li>\r\n            <li>Fillers</li>\r\n            <li>Cloze Test</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"box\">\r\n          <h4>General/Financial Awareness</h4>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Current Affairs</li>\r\n            <li>Banking Industry News</li>\r\n            <li>Awards and Honours</li>\r\n            <li>Books and Authors</li>\r\n            <li>Latest Appointments</li>\r\n            <li>Obituaries</li>\r\n            <li>New Government Schemes (Central/State)</li>\r\n            <li>Sports, etc.</li>\r\n            <li>Banking/Financial Terms</li>\r\n            <li>Static Awareness</li>\r\n            <li>Banking and Financial Awareness</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"box\">\r\n          <h4>Reasoning Ability</h4>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Internet</li>\r\n            <li>Machine Input/Output</li>\r\n            <li>Syllogism</li>\r\n            <li>Blood Relation</li>\r\n            <li>Direction Sense</li>\r\n            <li>Inequalities</li>\r\n            <li>Puzzles</li>\r\n            <li>Coding-Decoding</li>\r\n            <li>Ranking</li>\r\n            <li>Statement and Assumptions</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"box\">\r\n          <h4>Computer Aptitude</h4>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Basics of Computer (Hardware, Software, Generations)</li>\r\n            <li>DBMS</li>\r\n            <li>Networking</li>\r\n            <li>Internet</li>\r\n            <li>MS Office</li>\r\n            <li>Input-Output Devices</li>\r\n            <li>Important Abbreviations</li>\r\n            <li>Static GK (Country-Capital, Country-Currency, HQ of financial organizations, etc.)</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n      <div class=\"box\" style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\r\n        <h4>Static GK (Examples)</h4>\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>Country - Capital</li>\r\n          <li>Country - Currency</li>\r\n          <li>Headquarters of financial organizations / insurance companies</li>\r\n          <li>Constituencies of ministers</li>\r\n          <li>Dance forms</li>\r\n          <li>Nuclear and thermal power stations, etc.</li></ul></div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div></div></div><style>\r\n    body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;line-height:1.6;margin:20px;color:#111}\r\n    .wrap{max-width:950px}\r\n    .card{border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:10px;padding:14px;margin:14px 0}\r\n    h1{margin:0 0 10px}\r\n    p{margin:8px 0}\r\n    table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:10px}\r\n    th,td{border:1px solid #ddd;padding:8px;text-align:left;vertical-align:top}\r\n    th{background:#f6f6f6}\r\n    .note{background:#fff7e6;border:1px solid #ffe2a8;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin-top:10px}\r\n  </style>', 4, '2026-01-07 07:41:20', '2026-02-11 09:02:57'),
(29, 8, 'Eligibility Criteria', '\r\n\r\n\r\n<title>SBI SO Recruitment  Eligibility</title>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>SBI SO Recruitment Eligibility</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe eligibility criteria for SBI SCO vacancies to be filled through SBI SCO&nbsp; recruitment are detailed below. \r\nCandidates must fulfill eligibility conditions for the positions they apply for to qualify for further selection stages.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Educational Qualification</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe minimum educational qualification differs for each post. Details are provided below:\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody><tr>\r\n<th>Posts</th>\r\n<th>Educational Qualification</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>VP Wealth (SRM)</td>\r\n<td>\r\nMandatory: Graduation from a Government recognised University or Institution.<br><br>\r\nPreferred Qualification:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>MBA (Banking/Finance/Marketing) with 60% from recognized University or Institution.</li>\r\n<li>Certifications such as NISM V-A, XXI-A, CFP / CFA.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>AVP Wealth (RM)</td>\r\n<td>\r\nMandatory: Graduation from a Government recognised University or Institution.<br><br>\r\nPreferred:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Post-graduation in Finance / Marketing / Banking will be given weightage.</li>\r\n<li>Certifications such as NISM V-A, XXI-A, CFP / CFA.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Customer Relationship Executive</td>\r\n<td>\r\nGraduation from a Government recognised University or Institution.\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n\r\n<h3><br></h3><h3>Post-Qualification Experience&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody><tr>\r\n<th>Posts</th>\r\n<th>Post-Qualification Experience</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>VP Wealth (SRM)</td>\r\n<td>\r\nMandatory:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minimum 3 years experience in sales &amp; marketing with leading Public/Private/Foreign Banks, Wealth Management Firms, AMCs.</li>\r\n<li>SBI Wealth CREs having 4 years experience are also eligible.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nPreferred:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minimum 3 years experience as Relationship Manager or similar role in Wealth Management.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>AVP Wealth (RM)</td>\r\n<td>\r\nPreferred experience in documentation requirements of financial products and good communication skills.\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Customer Relationship Executive</td>\r\n<td>\r\nPreferred experience in documentation requirements of financial products and good communication skills.\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n\r\n<h3><br></h3><h3>Age Limit&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nCandidates must satisfy the post-wise minimum and maximum age criteria:\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody><tr>\r\n<th>Posts</th>\r\n<th>Minimum Age</th>\r\n<th>Maximum Age</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>VP Wealth (SRM)</td>\r\n<td>26 Years</td>\r\n<td>42 Years</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>AVP Wealth (RM)</td>\r\n<td>23 Years</td>\r\n<td>35 Years</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Customer Relationship Executive</td>\r\n<td>20 Years</td>\r\n<td>35 Years</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 2, '2026-01-07 07:41:20', '2026-02-17 11:00:32'),
(30, 8, 'Exam Pattern', '\r\n\r\n\r\n<title>SBI SO Exam Pattern 2025</title>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>SBI SO Exam Pattern</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nUnderstanding the structure of the exam and the sections involved is important for preparation. \r\nCandidates planning to appear for SBI SO&nbsp; must be familiar with the exam pattern and syllabus.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>SBI SO exam consists of <strong>Paper 1</strong> and <strong>Paper 2</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Paper 1 contains three sections to be completed within 90 minutes.</li>\r\n<li>Paper 2 includes questions from Professional Knowledge subjects.</li>\r\n<li>Qualifying marks are decided by the State Bank of India.</li>\r\n<li>Except the Professional Knowledge paper, other papers are qualifying in nature.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><br></h3><h3>SBI SO Exam Pattern Structure</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody><tr>\r\n<th>Paper</th>\r\n<th>Section</th>\r\n<th>No. of Questions</th>\r\n<th>Maximum Marks</th>\r\n<th>Duration</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td rowspan=\"3\">General Aptitude</td>\r\n<td>Test of Reasoning</td>\r\n<td>15</td>\r\n<td>15</td>\r\n<td rowspan=\"3\">45 Minutes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Quantitative Aptitude</td>\r\n<td>15</td>\r\n<td>15</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>English Language</td>\r\n<td>20</td>\r\n<td>20</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Professional Knowledge</td>\r\n<td>General IT Knowledge</td>\r\n<td>60</td>\r\n<td>100</td>\r\n<td>75 Minutes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 3, '2026-01-07 07:41:20', '2026-02-17 11:02:29'),
(31, 8, 'Exam Syllabus', '\r\n\r\n\r\n<title>SBI SO Syllabus 2025</title>\r\n\r\n<style>\r\nbody{\r\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\r\n    margin: 20px;\r\n    background: #f5f7fa;\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n.section{\r\n    background: #ffffff;\r\n    border: 1px solid #ddd;\r\n    border-radius: 6px;\r\n    padding: 15px;\r\n    margin-bottom: 20px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.section h3{\r\n    background: #e9eef5;\r\n    padding: 10px;\r\n    border-radius: 4px;\r\n}\r\n\r\nul{\r\n    columns: 2;\r\n    margin-top: 10px;\r\n}\r\n\r\nli{\r\n    margin-bottom: 6px;\r\n}\r\n</style>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>SBI SO Syllabus&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nBelow is the section-wise syllabus for SBI SO . Candidates should prepare topics from\r\nQuantitative Aptitude, Reasoning Ability, English Language, General IT Knowledge,\r\nand Role-Based Knowledge as required for the post.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h3>SBI SO Syllabus for Quantitative Aptitude</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Roots</li>\r\n<li>Bar Graphs</li>\r\n<li>Logarithms</li>\r\n<li>Probability</li>\r\n<li>Problems on Ages</li>\r\n<li>Time and Distance</li>\r\n<li>Line Graphs</li>\r\n<li>Problems on Trains</li>\r\n<li>Decimal &amp; Fractions</li>\r\n<li>Averages</li>\r\n<li>HCF &amp; LCM</li>\r\n<li>Percentages</li>\r\n<li>Mensuration</li>\r\n<li>Pie Charts</li>\r\n<li>Simplification</li>\r\n<li>Profit and Loss</li>\r\n<li>Clocks</li>\r\n<li>Mixtures &amp; Allegations</li>\r\n<li>Volume &amp; Surface Area</li>\r\n<li>Permutation &amp; Combination</li>\r\n<li>Time and Work</li>\r\n<li>Number System</li>\r\n<li>Boats &amp; Streams</li>\r\n<li>Pipes &amp; Cisterns</li>\r\n<li>Ratio and Proportions</li>\r\n<li>Simple &amp; Compound Interest</li>\r\n<li>Heights &amp; Distances</li>\r\n<li>Partnership</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h3>SBI SO Syllabus for Reasoning Ability</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Coding-Decoding</li>\r\n<li>Blood Relations</li>\r\n<li>Alphabet Test</li>\r\n<li>Sitting Arrangements</li>\r\n<li>Direction Sense Test</li>\r\n<li>Mathematical Operations</li>\r\n<li>Arithmetical Reasoning</li>\r\n<li>Logical Reasoning</li>\r\n<li>Analogy</li>\r\n<li>Classification</li>\r\n<li>Series</li>\r\n<li>Number, Ranking, and Time Sequence Test</li>\r\n<li>Eligibility Test</li>\r\n<li>Inserting the Missing Character</li>\r\n<li>Logical Sequence of Words</li>\r\n<li>Puzzle Test</li>\r\n<li>Alpha Numeric Sequence Puzzle</li>\r\n<li>Data Sufficiency</li>\r\n<li>Theme Detection</li>\r\n<li>Statement – Conclusions</li>\r\n<li>Clocks &amp; Calendars</li>\r\n<li>Number, Ranking &amp; Time Sequence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h3>SBI SO Syllabus for English Language</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reading Comprehension</li>\r\n<li>Idioms and Phrases</li>\r\n<li>Prepositions</li>\r\n<li>Tenses</li>\r\n<li>Conjunctions</li>\r\n<li>Active and Passive Voice</li>\r\n<li>One Word Substitution</li>\r\n<li>Synonyms and Antonyms</li>\r\n<li>Spotting the Error</li>\r\n<li>Cloze Test</li>\r\n<li>Grammar</li>\r\n<li>Fill in the Blanks</li>\r\n<li>Conclusion</li>\r\n<li>Passage Correction</li>\r\n<li>Subject-Verb Agreement</li>\r\n<li>Sentence Rearrangement</li>\r\n<li>Vocabulary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h3>SBI SO Syllabus for General IT Knowledge</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Working with Internet</li>\r\n<li>Operating System</li>\r\n<li>Cyber Security</li>\r\n<li>Software Packages</li>\r\n<li>MS Word &amp; Microsoft OneNote</li>\r\n<li>Microsoft Access</li>\r\n<li>Introduction to Computer Science</li>\r\n<li>Computer Networks</li>\r\n<li>Data Structures</li>\r\n<li>MS PowerPoint</li>\r\n<li>Spreadsheet</li>\r\n<li>Basic Computer Concepts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><b>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Part 2 of SBI SO Paper 2 (Professional Knowledge) includes questions from\r\nRole-Based Knowledge. Major subjects covered for different professional roles\r\nare listed below.</span>\r\n</b></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h3>SBI SO Syllabus for Chartered Accountant</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Accounting Standards and Guidance Notes</li>\r\n<li>Financial Reporting Standards</li>\r\n<li>Inflation Accounting</li>\r\n<li>Accounting and Reporting of Financial Instruments</li>\r\n<li>Indian Accounting Standards &amp; Corporate Financial Reporting</li>\r\n<li>Share-based Payment and Liability Valuation</li>\r\n<li>Share and Business Valuation</li>\r\n<li>Indian Capital Market</li>\r\n<li>Mutual Funds</li>\r\n<li>Foreign Exchange</li>\r\n<li>Auditing and related subjects</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h3>SBI SO Syllabus for System / IT Officer</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer Networks and Programming Languages (C, C++, Java)</li>\r\n<li>Computer Organization and Network Programming</li>\r\n<li>Algorithms and Digital Electronics</li>\r\n<li>Web Technologies</li>\r\n<li>Database Management Systems (DBMS)</li>\r\n<li>Basic Software and Hardware Concepts</li>\r\n<li>Data Structures</li>\r\n<li>Operating Systems &amp; System Programming</li>\r\n<li>Software Engineering</li>\r\n<li>Compiler Design</li>\r\n<li>Information Systems and Software Engineering</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h3>SBI SO Syllabus for Statistician</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basic Statistical Methods and Inference</li>\r\n<li>Uni-Variate &amp; Bi-Variate Data Analysis</li>\r\n<li>Variance Analysis</li>\r\n<li>Financial Market Concepts</li>\r\n<li>Simple and Multiple Regression</li>\r\n<li>Time-Series Forecasting</li>\r\n<li>Sampling Concepts</li>\r\n<li>Banking and Insurance</li>\r\n<li>Foreign Exchange and Portfolio Forecasting</li>\r\n<li>Sampling Distribution</li>\r\n<li>Estimation Theory</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>SBI SO Syllabus for Finance Officers</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Direct and Indirect Taxes</li>\r\n<li>Management Accounting Concepts</li>\r\n<li>Accounting Standards</li>\r\n<li>Auditing Standards</li>\r\n<li>Cost Accounting Concepts</li>\r\n<li>Basic Accounting Concepts and Principles</li>\r\n<li>Indian Capital Market</li>\r\n<li>Mutual Funds</li>\r\n<li>Foreign Exchange</li>\r\n<li>Auditing and related topics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h3>SBI SO Syllabus for Law Officers</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Banking Regulated Laws</li>\r\n<li>Negotiable Instruments</li>\r\n<li>Financial Analysis</li>\r\n<li>Banker-Customer Relationship</li>\r\n<li>Compliance and Legal Aspects</li>\r\n<li>Types of Securities</li>\r\n<li>Banking Security Laws</li>\r\n<li>Ethics and Corporate Governance in Banking</li>\r\n<li>Banking Operational Laws</li>\r\n<li>Electronic Banking</li>\r\n<li>Loans and Advances</li>\r\n<li>Regulatory Frameworks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<h3>SBI SO 2025 Marks Weightage</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe final merit list for SBI SO posts is prepared after normalization of marks\r\nobtained in the online written examination and interview in the ratio of 70:30 respectively.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody><tr>\r\n<th>Grades</th>\r\n<th>Written Test</th>\r\n<th>Interview</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>JMGS-I &amp; MMGS-II</td>\r\n<td>70%</td>\r\n<td>30%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 4, '2026-01-07 07:41:20', '2026-02-17 11:10:38');
INSERT INTO `bank_po_exam_tabs` (`id`, `exam_id`, `tab_title`, `tab_content`, `display_order`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(35, 9, 'Eligibility Criteria', '<h2 id=\"H64L7TJ6JK329KSPFU1DFQKRAS3IUUAX\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 28px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); display: inline-block; width: 892px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">RBI Grade B&nbsp; Eligibility Criteria</h2><h1 data-path-to-node=\"2\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, sans-serif !important; line-height: 1.15 !important;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; margin-block-end: 1em; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif;\">Candidates are required to follow the given&nbsp;<span style=\"text-align: center;\">RBI Grade B Syllabus</span>&nbsp;to be eligible for the upcoming RBI Grade B&nbsp; Exam<font color=\"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8)\" style=\"background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">:</font></p></h1><h3 style=\"line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.75rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">Educational Qualification</h3><h1 data-path-to-node=\"2\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, sans-serif !important; line-height: 1.15 !important;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">The grade-wise education qualification required to apply for various posts released under RBI Grade B Recruitment is discussed below.</p><figure class=\"table\" style=\"--bs-table-color: #212529; --bs-table-bg: transparent; --bs-table-border-color: #dee2e6; --bs-table-accent-bg: transparent; --bs-table-striped-color: #212529; --bs-table-striped-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); --bs-table-active-color: #212529; --bs-table-active-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); --bs-table-hover-color: #212529; --bs-table-hover-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.075); width: 892px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><table style=\"width: 892px;\"><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">RBI Grade B Educational Qualification</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Posts</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Minimum Educational Qualifications&nbsp;</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Officers in Grade \'B\' (DR) - (General)</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">• Graduation in any discipline /Equivalent technical or professional qualification with minimum 60% marks (50% for SC/ST/PwBD applicants) or Post-Graduation / Equivalent technical qualification with minimum 55% marks (pass marks for SC/ST/PwBD applicants) in aggregate of all semesters / years.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Note:</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">• Any such full-time course from a recognised University / Institute that is taken after Class XIIth and is at least of 3 years’ duration/ candidates possessing professional and technical qualifications which are recognised by the Government as equivalent to professional and technical graduation will be eligible for admission to the examination.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">• Candidates who have passed the Final Examination for Membership of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India may also apply for the post.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">OR</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">• Any such full-time course from a recognised University / Institute that is taken after graduation and is at least of 2 years’ duration / recognised by the Government as equivalent to post graduation will be eligible for admission to the examination.</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Officers in Grade \'B\' (DR) - DEPR</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">• Essential:</span>&nbsp;a. A Master\'s Degree in Economics / Econometrics / Quantitative Economics / Mathematical Economics / Integrated Economics Course/ Finance, with a minimum of 55% marks or an equivalent grade in aggregate of all semesters /years from a recognised Indian or Foreign University /Institute.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">OR</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">b. PGDM/ MBA Finance with a minimum of 55% marks or an equivalent grade in aggregate of all semesters /years from a recognised Indian or Foreign University /Institute.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">OR</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">c. Master’s Degree in Economics in any of the sub-categories of economics i.e. agricultural/ business/ developmental/ applied, etc., with a minimum of 55% marks or an equivalent grade in aggregate of all semesters /years from a recognised Indian or Foreign University /Institute</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">d. (i) Candidates having Master\'s Degree with Research/Teaching experience at a recognized Indian/Foreign University/ Institute will be eligible for relaxation in upper age limit to the extent of number of years of such experience subject to a maximum of three years. For experience, probationary period will not be reckoned.</p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Officers in Grade \'B\' (DR) - DSIM</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Essential:</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">a. A Master\'s Degree in Statistics/ Mathematical Statistics/ Mathematical Economics/ Econometrics/ Statistics &amp; Informatics from IIT-Kharagpur/ Applied Statistics &amp; Informatics from IIT-Bombay with a minimum of 55% marks or equivalent grade in aggregate of all semesters/years.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">OR</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">b. Master\'s Degree in Mathematics with a minimum of 55% marks or an equivalent grade in aggregate of all semesters / years and one-year post-graduate diploma in Statistics or related subjects from an Institute of repute.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">OR</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">c. M. Stat. Degree of Indian Statistical Institute with a minimum of 55% marks in aggregate of all semesters/years.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">OR</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; text-align: justify;\">d. Post Graduate Diploma in Business Analytics (PGDBA) jointly offered by ISI Kolkata, IIT Kharagpur and IIM Calcutta with a minimum of 55% marks or equivalent grade in aggregate of all semesters/years.</p></td></tr></tbody></table></figure></h1><h3 style=\"line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.75rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">Age Limit</h3><h1 data-path-to-node=\"2\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, sans-serif !important; line-height: 1.15 !important;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">RBI has defined minimum age criteria for appearing in the RBI Officer (Grade ‘B’) examination. Candidate must have attained the age of 21 years and must not have attained the age of 30, i.e., he/she must have been born not earlier than September 02, 1996, and not later than September 01, 2005, to apply for RBI Grade B Exam . The upper age limit for candidates possessing M.Phil. and PhD qualifications will be 32 and 34 years, respectively.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Age Relaxation</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">Candidates who belong to the reserved category will be provided relaxation in their upper age as per the rules decided by the Board.</p><figure class=\"table\" style=\"--bs-table-color: #212529; --bs-table-bg: transparent; --bs-table-border-color: #dee2e6; --bs-table-accent-bg: transparent; --bs-table-striped-color: #212529; --bs-table-striped-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); --bs-table-active-color: #212529; --bs-table-active-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); --bs-table-hover-color: #212529; --bs-table-hover-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.075); width: 892px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><table style=\"width: 892px;\"><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">RBI Grade B Age Limit Relaxation</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Category</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Age relaxation</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">SC/ST</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">5 years</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">OBC</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">3 years</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Physically Handicapped</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">10 years</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">PH + OBC</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">13 years</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">PH + SC/ST</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">15 years</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><ul style=\"padding-left: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><li><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">How many attempts can I give for RBI Grade B?</span><br>For the General Category- 6 attempts, and for SC/ST/OBC/PwBD categories- NO limit provided, the age criteria are met.</li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Which degree is best for RBI Grade B?</span><br>A graduation degree in any discipline or a Master\'s degree in Economics, Finance and Econometrics is desirable.</li></ul></h1><h2 id=\"YGYKKK4O5I4F40OBG36R04O7UWAWPCIQ\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 28px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); display: inline-block; width: 892px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"></h2>', 2, '2026-01-07 07:41:20', '2026-01-29 11:05:34');
INSERT INTO `bank_po_exam_tabs` (`id`, `exam_id`, `tab_title`, `tab_content`, `display_order`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(36, 9, 'Exam Pattern', '<h2 id=\"YEQ4LU1Q7PS8SEIXAYMRPYUVJOQB0OES\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 28px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); display: inline-block; width: 892px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">RBI Grade B&nbsp; Exam Pattern</h2><h5 class=\"pt20 bluc\" style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(0, 39, 87); font-size: 1.25rem; padding-top: 20px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; margin-block-end: 1em; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">Candidates are required to clear all three phases to get a confirmed post as a Grade B Officer in the Reserve Bank of India. The RBI Grade B exam is conducted in three phases: Phase I (Preliminary Exam), Phase II (Main Exam), and Phase III (Interview). Here\'s a detailed breakdown of the exam pattern:</p></h5><h3 style=\"line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.75rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">RBI Grade B Prelims Exam Pattern</h3><h5 class=\"pt20 bluc\" style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(0, 39, 87); font-size: 1.25rem; padding-top: 20px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">The prelims exam of RBI Grade-B Officer&nbsp; comprises a single Paper for 200 marks. A total time of 120 minutes will be given for answering. However, separate time will be allotted for each test.</p><figure class=\"table\" style=\"--bs-table-color: #212529; --bs-table-bg: transparent; --bs-table-border-color: #dee2e6; --bs-table-accent-bg: transparent; --bs-table-striped-color: #212529; --bs-table-striped-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); --bs-table-active-color: #212529; --bs-table-active-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); --bs-table-hover-color: #212529; --bs-table-hover-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.075); width: 892px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><table style=\"width: 892px;\"><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">RBI Grade B Prelims Exam Pattern</span></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"4\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Subject Names</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">General Awareness</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Quantitative Aptitude</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">English Language</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Reasoning</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">No. of Questions</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">200</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Total Marks</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">200</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Time Duration</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">2 Hours</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Note:</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; margin-block-end: 1em; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">A total time of 120 minutes will be given for the prelim exam. However, separate time will be allotted for each test. Detailed information regarding the examination will be given in an Information Handout, which will be made available for the candidates to download along with the call letter for the RBI Grade B&nbsp; prelims exam.</p></h5><h3 style=\"line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.75rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">RBI Grade B&nbsp; Mains Exam Pattern</h3><h5 class=\"pt20 bluc\" style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(0, 39, 87); font-size: 1.25rem; padding-top: 20px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">There are 3 papers for the Examination. Paper I Objective Type (on Statistics) and Papers II &amp; III will be descriptive type.</p><figure class=\"table\" style=\"--bs-table-color: #212529; --bs-table-bg: transparent; --bs-table-border-color: #dee2e6; --bs-table-accent-bg: transparent; --bs-table-striped-color: #212529; --bs-table-striped-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); --bs-table-active-color: #212529; --bs-table-active-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); --bs-table-hover-color: #212529; --bs-table-hover-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.075); width: 892px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><table style=\"width: 892px;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">S No</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Sections / Subjects</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Paper Type</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">No. of Questions</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Maximum Marks</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Duration (minutes)</span></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">1.</td><td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Paper I: Economics and Social Issues</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">50% Objective Type</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">30</td><td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">100</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">30 minutes</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">50% Descriptive</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">06 (to be attempted-4)</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">90 minutes</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">2.</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Paper II: English (Writing Skills)</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Descriptive</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">03</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">100</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">90 minutes</td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">3.</td><td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Paper III: Finance and Management</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">50% Objective Type</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">30</td><td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">100</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">30 minutes</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">50% Descriptive</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">06 (to be attempted-4)</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">90 minutes</td></tr></tbody></table></figure></h5><h3 style=\"line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.75rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">RBI Grade B Officer Interview Process</h3><h5 class=\"pt20 bluc\" style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(0, 39, 87); font-size: 1.25rem; padding-top: 20px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">Candidates will be shortlisted for the interview based on aggregate marks obtained in Paper-I, Paper II, and Paper III of the Phase II exam. The interview process will carry 50 marks.</p><ul style=\"padding-left: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><li><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Is RBI grade B phase 1 Qualifying?</span><br>Yes, candidates have to secure minimum marks separately for each test as well as in aggregate.</li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Is the RBI Grade B Interview tough to crack?</span><br>RBI Grade B Interview is considered challenging, and candidates must have a strong command of subject knowledge.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li></ul></h5><h2 id=\"BP7HVFKDNS2G3Q3QTL8EEY71TG3TK9HV\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 28px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); display: inline-block; width: 892px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">RBI Grade B&nbsp; Exam Preparation</h2><h5 class=\"pt20 bluc\" style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(0, 39, 87); font-size: 1.25rem; padding-top: 20px;\"><ul style=\"padding-left: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><li><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify;\">To score high in the RBI Grade B&nbsp; Exam, every candidate must look into the latest exam pattern and the changes in the syllabus so that preparation can be done accordingly. Candidates have the option to opt for the Offline Coaching Program offered by Career Power to enhance their skills. They can also solve Mock Test Papers to self-analyse and prepare judiciously for this upcoming exam. Follow the tips below to prepare for the RBI Grade B Officer Exam to score well.</p><ol style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem;\"><li>Take regular mock tests to understand the exam pattern and improve time management.</li><li>Practice previous year\'s question papers to understand the difficulty level and pattern of the questions asked.</li><li>Regularly revise the topics you have studied to ensure your efficiency when solving the questions from the topics.</li><li>Stay updated with the latest news, especially in the economy, finance, and banking.</li><li>For the English Descriptive Paper, practice essay writing, précis writing, and comprehension regularly.</li></ol></li></ul><p><ol style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem;\"></ol></p></h5><h2 id=\"YWCT34FK0S5YT4Q81O2JDBJHVTS5JNCR\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 28px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); display: inline-block; width: 892px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">RBI Grade B Exam Centres</h2><h5 class=\"pt20 bluc\" style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; line-height: 1.2; color: rgb(0, 39, 87); font-size: 1.25rem; padding-top: 20px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">The prelims exam will be conducted at the following exam centres nationwide. The candidates will be given a choice to select options of exam centres and then allotted their respective centres from the list of their preferred centres.</p><figure class=\"table\" style=\"--bs-table-color: #212529; --bs-table-bg: transparent; --bs-table-border-color: #dee2e6; --bs-table-accent-bg: transparent; --bs-table-striped-color: #212529; --bs-table-striped-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); --bs-table-active-color: #212529; --bs-table-active-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); --bs-table-hover-color: #212529; --bs-table-hover-bg: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.075); width: 892px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"><table style=\"width: 892px;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font color=\"#000000\">States /UTs</font></span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(99, 97, 107); background: rgba(49, 43, 71, 0.05); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Exam Centers for Prelims Exam</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Andaman &amp; Nicobar</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Port Blair</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Andhra Pradesh &amp; Telangana</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Guntur, Narasaraopet, Hyderabad, Rangareddy-Kodada, Karimnagar, Warangal, Rajahmundry, Kakinada, Tirupati, Chittoor, Vijaywada, Kanchikacherla, Gudlavalleru, Eluru, Vishakhapatnam, Vizianagaram</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Arunachal Pradesh</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Itanagar, Naharlagun city</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Assam</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Dibrugarh, Guwahati, Jorhat, Silchar</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Bihar</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; paddi