lor: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">15 minutes</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">4</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">English/Hindi Language</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">40</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">40</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">30 minutes</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">5</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">Quantative Aptitude</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">40</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">50</td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\">30 minutes</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Total</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">200</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">200</span></td><td style=\"padding-right: 5px; padding-left: 5px; border-color: rgb(64, 64, 64); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">2 hours</span></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p style=\"margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8); text-align: justify; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">A common exam (single exam) will be conducted for IBPS RRB Officer Scale-II &amp; III this year to select candidates based on their professional knowledge.</p><div><br></div><h2 id=\"GPEDF3DSGEN196TSUT4KHNN7B4TFLXTU\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 28px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); display: inline-block; width: 892px; background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\"></h2>', 0, '2026-01-31 09:02:44', '2026-01-31 09:03:30'),
(95, 17, 'Exam Syllabus', '\r\n\r\n<title>IBPS RRB Syllabus 2026 – Prelims &amp; Mains</title>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.5rem;\">IBPS RRB PO &amp; Clerk Syllabus&nbsp;</span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The syllabus mainly includes the following sections:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reasoning</li>\r\n<li>Quantitative Aptitude</li>\r\n<li>Computer Knowledge</li>\r\n<li>General Awareness</li>\r\n<li>English Language / Hindi Language</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><br></h3><h3>IBPS RRB Officer Scale II &amp; III Syllabus</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Officer Scale II (General Banking Officer) &amp; Scale III:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reasoning</li>\r\n<li>Quantitative Aptitude &amp; Data Interpretation</li>\r\n<li>Computer Knowledge</li>\r\n<li>Financial Awareness</li>\r\n<li>English Language / Hindi Language</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Officer Scale II (Specialist Cadre):</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reasoning</li>\r\n<li>Quantitative Aptitude &amp; Data Interpretation</li>\r\n<li>Computer Knowledge</li>\r\n<li>Professional Knowledge</li>\r\n<li>English Language / Hindi Language</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><br></h3><h3>IBPS RRB Syllabus for All Subjects</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nDetailed topics under each subject are provided below for candidates preparing for IBPS RRB Clerk and PO examinations.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"6\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody><tr>\r\n<th>Subjects</th>\r\n<th>Syllabus &amp; Topics</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Reasoning</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\nPuzzles &amp; Seating Arrangement, Number Series, Odd Man Out, Coding-Decoding,\r\nBlood Relation, Analogy, Syllogism, Alphabet Test, Ranking &amp; Time,\r\nCause &amp; Effect, Direction Sense, Figure Series, Word Formation,\r\nStatement &amp; Assumption, Assertion &amp; Reason,\r\nStatement &amp; Conclusion, Statement &amp; Arguments,\r\nStatements &amp; Courses of Action.\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Quantitative Aptitude / Numerical Ability</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\nNumber System, Data Interpretation (Bar, Line, Pie Charts), HCF &amp; LCM,\r\nProfit &amp; Loss, Simple &amp; Compound Interest, Time &amp; Work,\r\nTime &amp; Distance, Decimal &amp; Fraction, Averages,\r\nMensuration, Simplification, Partnership,\r\nPercentages, Ratio &amp; Proportion, Case Study DI,\r\nPermutation &amp; Combination, Probability.\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>General Awareness</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\nNational &amp; International Current Affairs, Sports,\r\nAbbreviations, Currencies &amp; Capitals, General Science,\r\nGovernment Schemes &amp; Policies, Banking Awareness,\r\nAwards &amp; Honors, RBI, Books &amp; Authors,\r\nNational Parks &amp; Sanctuaries.\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>English / Hindi Language</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\nReading Comprehension, Grammar/Vyakaran,\r\nSpotting Errors, Fill in the Blanks,\r\nMisspelled Words, Jumbled Words,\r\nSentence Rearrangement, Idioms &amp; Phrases,\r\nCloze Test, One Word Substitution,\r\nSynonyms &amp; Antonyms.\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Computer Knowledge</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\nFundamentals of Computers, History &amp; Future of Computers,\r\nInternet Basics, Networking, Hardware &amp; Software,\r\nShortcut Keys, MS Office, Database,\r\nSecurity Tools, Virus, Hacking, Trojans,\r\nInput &amp; Output Devices, Computer Languages.\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Financial Awareness</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\nCurrent Financial Events, Monetary Policy,\r\nBudget, Economic Survey, Banking Reforms,\r\nSpecial Bank Accounts, Loans,\r\nAsset Reconstruction Companies,\r\nNon-Performing Assets (NPA),\r\nLoan Restructuring, Risk Management,\r\nBASEL I, II, III,\r\nOrganizations like RBI, SEBI, IMF, World Bank, etc.\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 0, '2026-02-18 09:06:02', '2026-02-18 09:06:02');

